---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Section from '../components/Section.astro';
import Eyebrow from '../components/Eyebrow.astro';
import Todo from '../components/Todo.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Rubicon Workflows | About — Vancouver Automation Partner"
  description="A small, owner-led Vancouver automation consultancy. We solve real bottlenecks one step at a time, inside the tools you already use."
  surface="light"
>
  <!-- Forest hero — the brand-signature surface (brand doc: About page hero = Forest) -->
  <Section surface="forest">
    <header class="about-hero">
      <Eyebrow>About us</Eyebrow>
      <h1 class="about-hero__title">A small shop that solves real bottlenecks.</h1>
      <p class="about-hero__lede">
        For owner-led businesses with established operations, Rubicon Workflows is the
        automation partner that solves real bottlenecks one step at a time — because
        compounding small wins beats reinventing the system.
      </p>
    </header>
  </Section>

  <!-- Light body — reading surface -->
  <Section surface="light">
    <div class="prose">
      <h2>What we do</h2>
      <p>
        You know how every business has tasks that just eat hours — the weekly reports, the
        data entry, the back-and-forth between systems? We find those parts of your operation
        and automate them, so your team can focus on the work that actually matters. We work
        inside whatever systems you already use, starting with one bottleneck and building
        from there.
      </p>
      <p>
        The name's intentional — once you cross the Rubicon on a workflow, you don't go back
        to doing it the old way.
      </p>

      <h2>Who we work with</h2>
      <p>
        Small-to-mid-sized businesses — roughly 15 to 200 people — where the workflow we're
        automating impacts a team, not just an individual. Scale of impact matters more than
        size of company: a 15-person company where 10 people share the same workflow is a
        strong fit. Our clients are owner-operated companies in fields like construction,
        manufacturing, and strata management.
      </p>

      <h2>How we think about AI</h2>
      <p>
        We use AI when it's the right tool, not because it's a selling point. Many of our
        automations use deterministic code, API integrations, or scripted logic — often
        better than AI because they're predictable and don't hallucinate. When we do use AI,
        we say so plainly. When we don't, we don't pretend we do.
      </p>

      <h2>Who's behind it</h2>
      <p>
        <Todo label="team bios — names, roles, background (Content-Decisions #4)" />
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-hero {
    max-width: 46rem;
  }

  .about-hero__title {
    margin-top: var(--space-3);
    font-size: var(--text-display-l);
    line-height: var(--lh-display-l);
    letter-spacing: var(--track-display-l);
  }

  .about-hero__lede {
    margin-top: var(--space-6);
    font-size: var(--text-body-l);
    line-height: var(--lh-body-l);
    color: var(--muted);
  }
</style>
